{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Design provenance (2026-06-30): finalized via the joe-brainstorm protocol — OSS prior-art research (ESLint/Semgrep/RuboCop/Danger/OpenRewrite custom-rule registries; ArchUnit/dependency-cruiser/import-linter/deptrac invariant tools; Semgrep Structure-Mode / SonarQube / LangSmith Align-Evals authoring+calibration UX) + two codebase-grounding validation passes. Key grounded findings: (1) .rebar/detectors/ and .rebar/evals/ ALREADY give project-rule and project-fixture discovery, and the editor already authors criterion prompts — so net-new work is concentrated in the gate CONSUMER/wiring/preview seams, not authoring/engine. (2) criteria_routing.json is hand-maintained (its 'derived' docstring is aspirational; no generator/drift-gate). (3) claim_gate_check never re-compares the routing version, so attestation invalidation on criteria change must be added. (4) RISK: code-review (b744) is mid-rewrite adding a PARALLEL registry — decision: depend on b744, then unify into a shared rebar.llm.criteria layer."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782867413577617001,"uuid":"9f6c2102-3898-47ef-9de5-c689179994da"}